  {
   "fieldname": "assignment_note",
   "fieldtype": "HTML",
   "options": "<div class=\"form-message blue\">\n<strong>Why use this instead of Assignment Rules?</strong>\n<ol>\n<li><strong>Permission-aware:</strong> Each user can have individual permission filtering (Assignment Rules always ignore permissions)</li>\n<li><strong>Multiple assignments:</strong> Can assign to multiple users per document (Assignment Rules assign only one user)</li>\n<li><strong>Context-specific:</strong> Assignments are tied to specific review rules and their evaluation context</li>\n</ol>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Each user in the table has an \"Ignore Permissions\" checkbox. When unchecked, the user will only be assigned if they have submit permission on Document Review.</p>\n</div>"
